VER. 141.
But Umbriel, hateful Gnome! forbears not so;
He breaks the Vial whence the sorrows flow.] These two lines are additional; and assign the cause of the different operation on the Passions of the two Ladies. The poem went on before without that distinction, as without any Machinery to the end of the Canto. P.
